item.title: Carrie Underwood Posts Funny Pic 14 Years After 'American Idol' Win
item.description: Apparently, not even Carrie Underwood can look good while tearing up. The country singer posted a snapshot of herself on her Instagram Stories bawling her eyes out when she won American Idol more than a decade ago — and it’s hilarious. item.title: When Does Chainsaw Man Take Place?
item.description: Chainsaw Man takes place in 1997, but its 1997 era is vastly different from what occurred in the real-life world. This is due to the alternate timeline within which the entire story takes place. That alternate timeline makes the manga’s story bombastic in nature, but fans do not seem to mind as they have gobbled it up. Since its release in December 2018, Chainsaw Man has grown to become one of the bestselling mangas in the world and has spurned an anime, novel, stage play, and even an art exhibition.
